{
  "stem": "2522.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, nobody got mugged.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nobody got badly beaten up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I must also say that from my early youth, I was member of a fairly militant Jewish group.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we made sure that nobody got really mugged because we always went together as a fairly, fairly well-organized [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] troop.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The troop that I got associated with, I think, at the age of six, was Hashomer Hatzair, which was a very active group in Trencin.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hashomer Hatzair had a little house in the-- in the-- in the working district of Trencin.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had meeting rooms there, but also there were bedrooms for those who were preparing for the aliyah to Israel.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The, the Hashomer Hatzair building also had the schlichim from Israel who were professional organizers who came in and who supervised the, the, the young people who were learning a trade.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "By and large, the young teenagers, Jewish teenagers in Hashomer Hatzair--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--excuse me-- who were preparing for aliyah were learning a trade.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were apprenticed to, to the various trade groups in Trencin, particularly in machine building and the repair of agricultural machinery.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I, I must also mention that, that in 1940, when I could not go to school anymore, my father put me to work as an apprentice for-- to a machine shop, which repaired diesel engines that drove threshing machines.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so during the war from 1940 to 1941, I was following the track of those who were preparing for the aliyah.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My father always believed that an educated Jew should also have a trade.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I continue this with my children, as well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I, I would say that the Hashomer Hatzair, as I remember it, was one of militant, aggressive Zionism.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
